N2  - In this article the author presents a satirical study that attempts to display the irony of experiential learning groups. The author notes that these groups place great value on feelings, self-esteem and empathy and therefore can create pain and reduce the self-esteem of certain individuals through a lack of empathy. He bases his paper on pervious research that had examined the effects that learning groups on the psyche of various individuals, focusing on the difficulties that are encountered by individuals who favor thinking over feeling.
