N2  - In this article the author presents an evaluation of public policy and price discrimination vis-a-vis non-profit and profit seeking organizations. The author attempts to find out the circumstances under which a non-profit organization enjoys price discrimination advantages over a profit seeking organization. He notes that the larger policy issue following directly from this issue concerns the adjustment of the market place to favor the growth of non-profit organizations at the expense of capitalist organizations and other profit-seeking sectors of the economy.
